COVID IN INDIA
The COVID-19 pandemic has had a profound impact on India, affecting millions of lives and disrupting the economy. The country faced multiple waves of infections, with healthcare systems being overwhelmed during peak times. Efforts to combat the virus included nationwide lockdowns, mass testing, and a large-scale vaccination drive. Despite challenges, India has made significant progress in controlling the spread of the virus and vaccinating its population. Continuous vigilance and adherence to health guidelines remain crucial as the nation navigates the path to recovery.
